What is $\frac{0.\overline{3}}{0.8\overline{3}}$? Express your answer as a common fraction in lowest terms. ||| 
To find \frac{0.\overline{3}}{0.8\overline{3}}, we first convert both numbers:
\begin{align*}
0.\overline{3} &= 0.33333... = \frac{3}{9} = \frac{1}{3}, \
0.8\overline{3} &= 0.83333... = \frac{5}{6}. 
\end{align*}
Then we get:
\begin{align*}
\frac{0.\overline{3}}{0.8\overline{3}} &= \frac{\frac{1}{3}}{\frac{5}{6}} \
&= \frac{1}{3} \cdot \frac{6}{5} = \frac{6}{15} = \frac{2}{5}. 
\end{align*}
Hence, my answer is \boxed{\frac{2}{5}}.

