What is $8-4 \div 2-1$? ||| According to the order of operations, I will do the subtraction first and then the division. So, it will be: 
\begin{align*}
8-4 \div 2-1 &= 4 \div 2-1 \ 
&= 2-1 \ 
&= \boxed{1}.
\end{align*}

summary:
According to the standard order of operations, division occurs before subtraction. We find that our answer is \begin{align*}
8-4 \div 2 - 1 &= 8-2-1 \\
&= 6-1 \\
&= \boxed{5}.
\end{align*}

