The trisectors of angles $B$ and $C$ of scalene triangle $ABC$ meet at points $P$ and $Q$, as shown. Angle $A$ measures 39 degrees and angle $QBP$ measures 14 degrees. What is the measure of angle $BPC$?

[asy]unitsize(2cm);
label("$B$",(0,0),W);

label("$A$",(1.2,1.5),N);
label("$C$",(1,0),E);
label("$Q$",(.8,.6),N);
label("$P$",(.7,.2),N);

draw((0,0)--(1.2,1.5)--(1,0)--cycle,linewidth(1));
draw((0,0)--(.8,.6)--(1,0),linewidth(1));
draw((0,0)--(.7,.2)--(1,0),linewidth(1));
[/asy] ||| To find the angles in triangle ABC, we know angle A is 39 degrees and angle QBP is 14 degrees. First, if we consider angle ABC as 14 degrees, then angle ACB should be 180 - 14 - 39 = 127 degrees. Then, since angle ABC = 14, angle BPC is simply 180 - 14 - 127 = 39 degrees. Thus, the measure of angle BPC is \boxed{39} degrees.

