label("$D$",(0,0),S);
label("6",(3,0),N);
draw((0,0.4)--(0.4,0.4)--(0.4,0));
[/asy] Therefore, triangle $ABC$ has a base of length $9$ and a height of length $4.$ Thus, the area of triangle $ABC$ is $$\frac{1}{2}bh = \frac{1}{2}(9)(4) = \frac{1}{2}(36) = \boxed{18}.$$

